SKILL|requesting-code-review|"Pre-commit review: security scan, quality gates, auto-fix."
STEP|1|Core principle:** No agent should verify its own work. Fresh context finds what you miss.
STEP|2|After implementing a feature or bug fix, before `git commit` or `git push`
STEP|3|When user says "commit", "push", "ship", "done", "verify", or "review before merge"
STEP|4|After completing a task with 2+ file edits in a git repo
STEP|5|After each task in subagent-driven-development (the two-stage review)
STEP|6|Skip for:** documentation-only changes, pure config tweaks, or when user says "skip verification".
STEP|7|This skill vs github-code-review:** This skill verifies YOUR changes before committing.
STEP|8|Test frameworks** (auto-detect by project files):
STEP|9|Linting and type checking** (run only if installed):
STEP|10|Baseline comparison:** If baseline was clean and your changes introduce failures,
STEP|11|[ ] No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials
STEP|12|[ ] Input validation on user-provided data
STEP|13|[ ] SQL queries use parameterized statements
STEP|14|[ ] File operations validate paths (no traversal)
STEP|15|[ ] External calls have error handling (try/catch)
STEP|16|[ ] No debug print/console.log left behind
STEP|17|[ ] No commented-out code
STEP|18|[ ] New code has tests (if test suite exists)
STEP|19|security_concerns non-empty -> passed must be false
STEP|20|logic_errors non-empty -> passed must be false
STEP|21|Cannot parse diff -> passed must be false
STEP|22|Only set passed=true when BOTH lists are empty
STEP|23|All passed:** Proceed to Step 8 (commit).
STEP|24|Any failures:** Report what failed, then proceed to Step 7 (auto-fix).
STEP|25|Maximum 2 fix-and-reverify cycles.**
STEP|26|Passed: proceed to Step 8
STEP|27|Failed and attempts < 2: repeat Step 7
STEP|28|Failed after 2 attempts: escalate to user with the remaining issues and
STEP|29|subagent-driven-development:** Run this after EACH task as the quality gate.
STEP|30|test-driven-development:** This pipeline verifies TDD discipline was followed —
STEP|31|plan:** Validates implementation matches the plan requirements.
STEP|32|**Empty diff** — check `git status`, tell user nothing to verify
STEP|33|**Not a git repo** — skip and tell user
STEP|34|**Large diff (>15k chars)** — split by file, review each separately
STEP|35|**delegate_task returns non-JSON** — retry once with stricter prompt, then treat as FAIL
STEP|36|**False positives** — if reviewer flags something intentional, note it in fix prompt
STEP|37|**No test framework found** — skip regression check, reviewer verdict still runs
STEP|38|**Lint tools not installed** — skip that check silently, don't fail
STEP|39|**Auto-fix introduces new issues** — counts as a new failure, cycle continues
STEP|40|**React hooks rules-of-hooks violations** — calling `useCallback`/`useState`/`useEffect` inside
PIT|**Empty diff** — check `git status`, tell user nothing to verify
PIT|**Not a git repo** — skip and tell user
PIT|**Large diff (>15k chars)** — split by file, review each separately
PIT|**delegate_task returns non-JSON** — retry once with stricter prompt, then treat as FAIL
PIT|**False positives** — if reviewer flags something intentional, note it in fix prompt
PIT|**No test framework found** — skip regression check, reviewer verdict still runs
PIT|**Lint tools not installed** — skip that check silently, don't fail
PIT|**Auto-fix introduces new issues** — counts as a new failure, cycle continues
PIT|**React hooks rules-of-hooks violations** — calling `useCallback`/`useState`/`useEffect` inside